caption: Gorgeous, private, quiet patio and delicious food! I highly recommend their housemate gnocchi and the risotto. Photos also include lamb, although I didn’t think it was quite worth the portion size.  IG also has an amazing bar— every drink (alcoholic and non), I’ve always greatly enjoyed. worth the money!
very small plates. over priced but a good date site.
Spectacular service! Customer-centered. And most importantly, delicious for a good price. Also great veg/vegan options.

My experience was embarrassing and uncomfortable. My husband and I enjoy traveling and dinning all restaurants and exploring the menu and embracing the experience. Unfortunately for us we were 2nd class and not treated fairly. The reservation was books weeks in advance and I reached out a few days in advance to learn about the chef’s table. The communication with the restaurant was difficult and a poor website to navigate - it was hard to truly plan this special occasion. I tried to call again the day before my reservation- no response. I luckily receive a call to confirm my reservation and I inquire about the chef table and the information was available and I was expecting a call back. However I didn’t receive a call back so once we checked-in with  hostess, I inquired again. Immediately learning it was the individual I spoke with and said she’ll provide the information shortly. We were told a table wasn’t ready and we had no problem waiting. While waiting 20 minutes past our reservation we didn’t receive any information. Once our table was available- we were sat on a table that was squeezed onto the terrace that didn’t provide enough heat for a comfortable experience. The table was on a 45 degree angle and slightly impossible to eat a meal. Finally after learning that the chef menu is a variety of the standard menu it was ridiculous. It went from being flexible about not having our table ready to an overall sour experience. Anna happened to be proactive and professional and I appreciate her transparency- but it’s not my responsibility as a guest. The experience is tarnished thus far and the concept and style of this restaurant should have executed this experience seamless. Instead we felt thrown into a last resort table - sat late on reservations... super frustrating when having a babysitter and short flexibility. Time should be respected and I know with Covid everything is adjusting but don’t squeeze tables without considering all circumstances. We never ate.
Nice food
Love the food here and the staff here are awesome. I highly recommend you try this place out. And portion sizes are huge too.
(Translated by Google) good  (Original) جيد

Amazing service. Outstanding drinks. The food was a disappointment.  We had a reservation at Iron Gate for a Friday date night (dating anniversary) We waited about 15 minutes even with a reservation. Had the paw paw bear while waiting and loved it. The ambience was great and the seat heaters was a nice touch. They had one of the best negroni I’ve had.  Our server recommended the tasting menu and we went with that. The tasting menu had nothing that was outstanding. We expected something unique or adventurous from a restaurant with a star. Our server explained the menu for the table to be an extraordinary affair so we were understandably disappointed when we were served under seasoned cabbage salad.  The regular menu was seafood heavy but that wasn’t the case with the tasting menu. The only notable seafood was in a salad. We really expected more than one seafood appetizer and one meat in the main.  Furthermore, we were supposed to receive 5 mains according to the server but were only served 4. The mains included a kale Caesar salad, we’re not the biggest fans of kale and expected more than that for a tasting menu.  Another great disappointment was the suggested wine pairing for our mains. We only wanted one glass and the server suggested a red which absolutely didn’t go well with the food.  Lastly, the dessert was rice pudding. Again, why is it on the tasting menu of a restaurant with a star.  I am greatly disappointed to have spent $300+ on a dinner for 2 and received this selection of food. If we knew what the tasting menu was like we would have definitely gone ala crate .  I was really keen on trying their seafood and would love to go back and assume this was a one off experience but $300 for 2 is a substantial amount of money and to me it feels like a waste.
Such a gorgeous ambiance for winter outdoor dining! Wonderful staff, INCREDIBLE food, great drinks! If you need a hot, COVID date spot, this is a good one!
We attended a small wedding reception here outdoors, during covid. Great food and extraordinary staff.  Ambience was perfect.
Great ambiance
One of the best meals we've ever had. Highly recommend the family table. Every dish was incredible, especially the luxurious focaccia bread.
Delectable but will literally bankrupt you.
Expensive and delicious. Treat yourself!

Honestly felt like the food for the thanksgiving courses was a bit bland, and just not really satisfying. It was pretty mediocre. And we came hungry. they also included a 22% gratuity into our bill which made me cringe. I don’t mind tipping extra especially during a pandemic and am a server myself but I feel like that’s just kind of rude but whatever
We went for the Thanksgiving dinner and we were so impressed!! The service, food, and ambiance were just over the top! Highly recommend!
I’ve dinned at this restaurant over a dozen times. While the food hasn’t decline the service has. They are rude and dismissive. I would avoid this restaurant until it is resolved.
Loved the outdoor ambiance.  The Chef's Family Table was amazing and was the highlight of our birthday celebration!

Okay let’s start with the good. Ambiance is immaculate. The outdoor seating is gorgeous and comforting. The gnocchi and beet salad was very good.  The bad. Holy c*ap the service was awful. Our waiter was very inattentive. We ordered drinks, 20 minutes later he comes back to the table to let us know that the drink are “sold out.” Our apps take ages to come out. Swordfish was too salty. We had to ask two different staff members for our check because our waiter was no where to be found.
Excellent service, great food, we went with the chef's choice and everything that came out topped the last plate.  Excited to go back.

Iron gate made our night truly unforgettable. They were so careful around Covid protocols (which seems unfortunately rare) and the food was FANTASTIC. They went over the top when they found out it was our anniversary, and even ended the meal with a hand-written thank you note.  I can't recommend them highly enough!

The restaurant setting is very nice. However, when we first sat down our host told us there is a 1 hour and 15 minute time limit. We were like OK seems short, but that should be enough time. Our server comes by never gives us his name or appears interested at all in conversing with us. It took 30 minutes for our food to come. When it finally did we had 20 minutes left on our time to order anything else. Our server would keep passing right by us and never asked how our food was, never asked if we needed anything else. We would actively look around like we needed something and our table was right next to the kitchen, so it should have occurred to him to check in with us. but he didn't. A very nice gentleman saw that we were looking around and asked what we needed and he brought it. Our server never returned to our table except at the end to clear our table and bring our check (we kept thanking him, and he had no response). When we do get the check we see a 22% automatic gratuity (I think for COVID). In any other setting it would be fine, but our server did not come over more than once. So the fact that they put an automatic 22% for next to no service was annoying. I asked to speak to a manager and she did accommodate us . But my intention wasn't too get free stuff, it was to say that time of service is absolutely unacceptable for a place that is so highly regarded. Overall, the service alone would probably make me never go back.

Iron Gate takes covid precautions very seriously. The tables were at least 6 ft apart on the patio where we sat, you must put your mask back on when a server comes to your table, which nobody should be opposed to. Our server was new, but very professional and patient. They knew it was our anniversary, and they brought out a free mini appetizer, a happy anniversary ice cream bar, and a couple flutes of prosecco.  This was our third anniversary dinner at Iron Gate, and they always go above and beyond. They even gave us a handwritten anniversary card. We were sad that the squid ink pasta and lobster dish is no longer on the menu, but we understand that covid has forced most restaurants to reduce their menu offerings.  The focaccia was excellent. The fritters were solid, although I would probably skip them next time. The romanesco wedge salad was very good, although a little small. My partner had the mushroom pasta, which she enjoyed very much, and which came with a ton of noodles. My gnocchi dish was also excellent, and also came with a ton of gnocchi. We had the apple Napoleon dessert, whose name eludes me, which was also very good. payment is completely contactless, so you scan a QR code on the receipt and pay through your phone. A 22% gratuity is automatically added right now, and the server pointed that out for us.  A very good experience as always.
Great food, order the bold and delicious bourbon cocktail

We’ve been going to Iron Gate since 2014 and have loved every meal since the first. Tonight was our first dinner out in DC since March (thank you quarantine/Covid). And what better restaurant to go to than our #1..Iron Gate. It was incredible. Safe, clean, romantic, delicious, special. Crystal was fantastic and the food was better than we remembered. Get the focaccia, autumn squash, gnocchi and shrimp and blue crab giovetsi .. you won’t regret it. Get a reservation ASAP and get a cocktail and bottle of wine. Treat yourself..you deserve it and Iron Gate will deliver.

Food was excellent! We ate in the wisteria covered patio which was very cute.  COVID REVIEW They have a QR code menu, but thankfully you still place your order with a server. They do make you put your mask in everytime the server comes, which is a pain that definitely interrupts the dining experience. Still though, food was good and they're doing the best they can.
Fun small plates. Focaccia is interesting and amazing. Gnocchi is a must, along with the octopus

Food always great. Lovely ambiance. The service is hit or miss. This time, it took a long time to get our entrees and and the waiter was rather curt, unhelpful and inattentive. We sat out front instead of on the patio so maybe ...
Worst service and most uncomfortable experience being forced to eat and drink with mask and then the put a 22% tip on a 3 person table.  A joke

Went here to celebrate my birthday. Good food and nice outdoor atmosphere - but the service completely ruined the experience. Not friendly or accommodating at all, they didn’t ask us if we dined there before, they didn’t run through the menu or make any recommendations. In fact they didn’t even have a menu, we had to pull it up on our smartphone. They refused to make me an old fashioned, despite the fact that they have a full bar they would inly make one of their 5 or 6 specialty cocktails. They should also provide disposable paper menus for those that don’t have (or want to use) their phone. They also didn’t clean off dirty appetizer plates from the table before bringing the next course. They awkwardly wouldn’t get within 6’ of the table without everyone putting their masks on, even if we were in the middle of eating or drinking or talking, which really makes it hard to have a fun dinner. Really just a bad experience, and COVID is no excuse for any of this, I’ve eaten at 25+ DC restaurants for sit-down dinners since COVID started, and none of them are doing the strange and uninviting measures that Iron Gate has implemented.
Great food, drinks and atmosphere!

What I love most about this spot is the ambiance..The always changing menu will seem limited but it’s rich in flavor and creativity. Sharing dinner here with 4-6 people, you could order the entire menu and get a taste of everything with out leaving too full. Wine list is extensive and cocktails are creative.  Reason it gets 4 stars: I’ve dined here 5 times over 2 years I get very mixed experiences from the people working, sometimes it’s snobby interactions and other times it’s been super warm genuine hospitality.
Beautiful atmosphere, great food, wonderful staff and service. They also do covid dining right.

The place is nice, the food is definitely good, however, I was seated in a table looking over the service area and the mess inside, nothing concealing the room other than a curtain with a questionable style, not visually pleasing. Also, during Covid, high standards are great and appreciated, then again, having to wear the mask everytime someone approaches the end of a big table is a bit of an overkill, Extremly disruptive to the atmosphere. It might be easier to just wear the mask and go pick the food up myself instead of continuous interruption. Lastly, they do their billing online and they add extra for graduity in additon to a mandatory tip- really?  Overall, the food is good but not good enough to worth all of the hassle.

The best pandemic dining out experience I’ve had so far! They have the best atmosphere in normal times, and that holds true even with social distancing protocols.  Really appreciated all the care they took, and that they had you put the mask on when the staff comes to the table. At other restaurants I have never know what is right to do or not!  Given that it’s a sharing plates restaurant, wouldn’t recommend going with anyone outside of your “pod.” I’ve been eagerly waiting for them to reopen and was not disappointed
come here every year for birthday celebration. food and experience gets better every visit
Very good place. Octopus was very soft and extremely good.  Highly recommend this restaurant for everyone.

FOOD POISONING: I received food poisoning here earlier this year.  Took me a week to recover, during which I missed school.  I had to go to urgent care, as I was projectile vomiting and/or having diarrhea every 15-20 minutes.  I incurred hundreds of dollars worth of medical bills due to this visit to urgent care.  I was in horrible pain, and eventually began to vomit up just stomach acid.  Urgent care nurses had to inject some medicine into my bloodstream to tackle the nausea.  They told me the pills they would prescribe me wouldn’t work fast enough.  I was weak and didn’t return fully to normal until around a week later.  Lost 5 lbs in one night.  Iron Gate management was contacted, but never returned the voicemail.  I’ve never sued anyone, but considering the hundreds of dollars in medical bills I’ve incurred due to THEIR FAULT, and their lack of acknowledgement, something needs to be done so more patrons don’t get food poisoning.  It looks like they might go out of business anyway.  They certainly deserve it.
My favorite dish from here is their olive leaf wrapped rice tomatine.
One of my favorite date spots in DC! Make sure to sit outside if the weather permits

As you walk true the half restaurant u will reach to an amazing cosy place with a  highlight of a fire place . Great service and the food is excellent unbelievable yummy . Try out there fresh grapefruit juice it is a vitamin bomb .
Really great food, service, presentation, and drink choices. Listen to the wait staff for good suggestions.
(Translated by Google) In 1 word DELICIOUS !!!  (Original) In 1 woord HEERLIJK!!!

Really cool, old school spot in mid city near dupont.  Food is classy but tasty and not over done.  Cozy spot for a nice day on the patio, or nice calm interior with a giant fireplace on a not so nice day.
Food was absolutely delicious. Eash course raised the favor bar for the next. Zack our server was very knowledgeable and friendly. Go with the 11 dish chef's choice. Tou won't be disappointed.
Definitely one some of the best food that I've had in DC, plus it is in a really cool location.

Stopped in for brunch at the bar. It was a rainy sunday. Got a whiskey sour and I think an egg & salad. One of the best whiskey sours I've ever had. Good coffee. Great service. Polite and attentive. Very cool back patio area and a whole other section in the back that was bustling.

My boyfriend and I went to Iron Gate for the first time to celebrate my birthday. I had heard so many great things about the ambiance and food, so it was on my DC food bucket list. This place deserves a five star rating because Jenny was an absolutely wonderful server,  but the hostess ruined that chance. Having worked in a five star fine dining restaurant for several years, I expect to always receive a warm greeting and interaction with a host/hostess. When we arrived there were two other couples ahead of us waiting to be seated, so we patiently waited to the side as not to crowd the very small space. While the hostess seated the second couple, Jenny had come to the front and checked us in and assured we would be seated when the hostess got back. Two other couples arrived after us, and when the hostess returned she seemed to ignore our existence (felt as though it was due the fact we were the youngest couple present). The couple she began to try to help acknowledged we had arrived first, so the hostess then turned to my boyfriend and snappishly asked how she could help us. Taken aback by the attitude my boyfriend did not answer immediately, and then she turned back to the other couple. He then spoke up, and she seemed to struggle to find our reservation. Luckily, Jenny came back up to the host stand at that point and showed that she had already checked us in. Jenny asked her if she could show us to whatever table, and the hostess gave her attitude saying "no, they can either sit on the patio or right here" gesturing to the tables next to the host stand. I immediately said we would sit outside, and Jenny let us have our pick of a table. It was very obvious that I was quite annoyed at that point, and Jenny did everything she could to try to remedy what happened. Overall, the food was amazing, compliments to the kitchen, and our server was superb. I was very excited to try this restaurant. I just wish we had a better first impression, and maybe I would have enjoyed the first half of our dining experience more.

FOOD POISONING. Dined there Friday 2/7/2020 at 6pm. Food, service, and atmosphere were great- until my wife and I got horrible food poisoning to the point where she had to go to the hospital... Completely ruined our weekend, and made my wife sick for 3 days. I would never expect this from a place where my bill totaled $200... We know it happened there as we both barely made it home without throwing up. I called the office and they seemed somewhat responsive and sympathetic - they offered to give us a free meal (at a different restaurant). It's been a few days and they still haven't reached back out to us. I'm leaving this review up until they do...

My wife and I recently visited for our second time. It was just as good as the first, if not better! We were visiting for our wedding anniversary and the server, Kevin, was kind enough to share a free class of champagne for the occasion. But that's not all! Kevin was an amazing person and sever. He was very familiar with the wine and menu.  Because of him, my wife and I had an amazing stay at Iron Gate.
The brunch was really great. I've had scallops and it was delicious.
Good cuisine, but a bit pricey with crowded seating.  Nice staff.

The food was great, as well as the wine list. But the service was awful, truly - long excruciating waits for everything, and bad attitude when complaining. Yet, the prices were pretty high and it wasn't worth it at all!
Not that good.
Amazing vibe, feels like an escape from the city while being right in the heart of it. Highly recommend for dinner or drinks.
I was shocked to have a snappy reaction from a waitress when I pointed out that she opened me the wrong bottle of wine. Very nice staff Highly recommended.

It was restaurant week and I'm so glad I got to eat here for it! It was a three course meal for $22, amazing. I had the arancini balls which were light and fluffy with a mushroom creme sauce that I could eat a whole bowl of. Next was the gnocchi with spicy Pomodoro sauce. It had a nice kick and the gnocchi was perfectly cooked. Desert was an orange tart ice cream and marshmallow , also amazing. This place had familiar flavors that were perfectly executed. Nothing showy or fancy, just really good ingredients cooked incredible well and balanced to perfection. Also, get the cocktails!
Fantastic food and ambiance at a relatively reasonable price. Three of us ate and split a bottle of wine for only ~$150.

The cremini mushroom arancini was crispy and deliciously creamy on the inside.    I could have eaten a whole plateful.  The crispy blue catfish was very good with the kohlrabi-apple salad, but wasn't satisfying as an entree.  Had they turned it into a sandwich or had a small side it would have helped.  The blood orange tart was really good.  This was my 8th Restaurant Week lunch and the first time I left the restaurant hungry after eating my meal.

Lousy service. There were multiple tables available when we got there. But the maitre d simply said they can't seat us without offering any explanation. It appears that they are not eager to have guests. Won't go there anymore...
Cool restaurant

Neat place with great drinks, great food, and great service.  The sourdough bruschetta was amazing.  We had a salad of some kind that my wife didn't like but I thought was decent.  We had lobster pasta.  My wife didn't like the lobster- I thought it was ok, but not outstanding.  The pasta and sauce were incredible, though.
Fantastic food! Nice atmosphere. Recommended!
Delightful. Great restaurant week menu.
Amazing lobster and black pasta! Can't wait to come back here during Restaurant week to try something new!
Great menu selection,the food was beautifully cooked, had wonderful hostess made the she experience more enjoyable. Small plate style worth it
I have been here with my family,food is very good!!!
Great ambiance! Food is OK, but too much emphasis is placed on the spices, sauces, etc rather than the intrinsic tastes and qualities of the food itself.
Great
Seven fishes dinner so good, even discerning foodie friends were impressed. Courteous service at the table. Wonderful bar. We had a great evening.
Lovely bar and outside patio. Amazing food, cocktails, and service. Implausible to have a bad experience here.

More hits than misses at this Mediterranean inspired small plates restaurant. Lots of experimentation makes for always interesting combinations and the evolving cocktail list is another stand out. The service is good but not pushy, perfect for a quiet date night. The multiple dining rooms ensure that you have a variety of experiences to select from, from lively long tables to intimate two tops to bar seating. In an area of town replete with excellent cooking Iron Gate may not always grab the most attention, but it more than holds its own.
Amazing food and service in an incredibly cool, yet romantic atmosphere. Definitely check this place out!
Incredible food in an intimate setting.
Although a little pricey this place has great food and even better service. Great place for a date night!

I went to Iron Gate on a weeknight, specifically to drink at their bar. It’s a great environment for a date night because of the low lighting and chill background music that isn’t too loud, so you can have a nice conversation with a relaxing ambiance. I like this bar because they have a huge selection of top shelf liquor and their bartenders do a great job crafting any classic (e.g. a martini or old fashioned) to your liking, along with a nice selection of their own unique specialty cocktails. There’s also a huge wine selection, and you can order any food from their restaurant while at the bar. I definitely want to go back for a dinner. The dining area is a patio (heated during the winter) that’s covered with a beautiful trellis filled with vines. A very quaint and relaxing vibe.

Great food, but the lunch prices were a little high. The menu is mostly small plates, and they recommend 2-3 per person, which adds up. Three small plates, plus a drink and dessert was about $53, plus tip.  The outdoor area has fire pits & blankets in the fall/winter. Pacing at lunch was also off. They served the burger (which didn't have enough of the excellent house-made kettle chips) within 2min of the appetizer. Try the donuts!

Would have left a much better review had we been seated within half an hour of a reservation, but that didn’t happen. Had an 8:15 dinner reservation on a Wednesday night and was seated around 8:55. Everything else was fine-the food was beautiful, the wait staff knowledgeable, the space cozy-but the 40 minutes of waiting around really ruined the experience.
very fancy. not a regular spot for me but a must for foodies in DC.
Excellent atmosphere. Good food. The main room is very cozy.
It doesn't look like much from the outside but it's beautiful inside and very romantic. The food was delicious. Try the gnocchi!

Very sprightly menu lots of raw veggies with nuts. Example: duo dip, ground walnuts with beets and ground parsley with almonds served with fennel seed crackers...fried Blue fish over a complex salad w/ oil cured olives, pistachios and fennel was excellent. Didn't have reservations for lunch so could only appreciate the pretty backroom with fireplace for next time. Instead ate ( the first day of chilly winter) in the freezing bar area and sat with a hat on. I and the people next to me at the bar all had hot tea... We commented as it was easily 50 degrees. MAKE A RESERVATION!
Wow. The atmosphere of this restaurant may be enough to warrant a visit. Good thing the food is fantastic as well 👌
Food was good. Great services. Great atmosphere. Staff were nice.
Food was good. Services was great. Atmosphere was good. Great facility was provided. Great presentation of food.
Limited menu options during brunch but overall good service and great atmosphere.
Lovely place, great food, relaxed ambiance
Brunch was delicious. Great service and good. Inside is small but the outside tables are perfect.
Amazing, utterly amazing food! Not cheap but you get what you pay for! Recommend a full three courses and sharing plates so you can try a bit of everything.
Atmosphere and food are excellent.

Had a very pleasant lunch with son here. Hostess and wait staff (Gabe) were very friendly. We both had the gyro and shared the apple crumble for dessert. The gyro had a wonderful smokey flavor to the pork. Quite intimate atmosphere  with nice patio area. Recommend.

We went for brunch today. The place is huge elegant and classy. Kinda laid back. My boyfriend had to catch a flight and we could have helped me a faster service. But the delicious food made up! My second drink was dunning late so we cleared the bill but the drink arrived as we were leaving. Server was gracious enough to say we could either drink it on the house or leave. We left but really like the gesture! The sausages and pancakes really stuck out! Drinks and ambiance are top notch!
Food is good but we waited for a long time!
Lovely. Great food, romantic ambiance, friendly service.
Great restaurant in DuPont Circle. Upscale vibe with a local seasonal menu. Outdoor space is truly amazing.

Had a great experience at brunch for a friend's birthday. The outdoor patio is totally magical and perfect for intimate dining. The food was really delicious (get the doughnuts if you know what's good for you), the cocktails were delightful and the service was impeccable.
Loved it! Great for a date or a special ocasion, it is not cheap but the food is worth it

We attended a wedding, which is usually not a good time to judge a kitchen, but I was pleasantly surprised. They produced an outstanding salmon dish plus delicious roasted vegetables. Desserts were excellent. We will soon try it for dinner

(Translated by Google) It was not bad, but it was not what I expected, very nice place, the prices were not so bad, but the portions very small.  (Original) No estuvo mal, pero no fue lo que esperaba, muy lindo lugar, los precios no estaban tan mal, pero las porciones muy chicas.

Amazing 5* outside patio! Great to sit and eat! Atmosphere and Ambiance is neat, comfortable and elegant. The restaurant appears super clean. Servers are pleasant, communicative, efficient and knowledgeable. And most importantly the food is nicely presented, taste was good. The mix of “chefs family table” was not what we expected, but generally good food.

GREAT restaurant! Went here for restaurant week after hearing all the great reviews. It certainly lived up to the hype. The food was great, and what was maybe even better was the ambience. This is a terrific spot for a date. Our service wasn't very good, but the food and atmosphere made up for it. I will definitely be back.
Lovely bar and outside patio. Amazing food, cocktails, and service. Implausible to have a bad experience here.
Love this place. Intimate, good food, and great service.

We really enjoyed the food here. My daughter loved their buttered noodles as they season them really well. Ravioli was excellent too. Two issues though. One we made a reservation and when we got there all they had was their patio seating which can get hot and has some mosquitoes. Luckily we found a very tight spot in the bar area that wasn't very comfortable but at least inside. Second we ordered a shirley temple (7-up and cherry juice or grenadine) for my daughter but they served us some specialty version mocktail that was $8 without telling us which she didn't like and didn't drink and I didn't realize was $8 till I got the bill.
Fabulous Brunch! Recommended by Thrillist as one of the best brunches in town...and we 100% agree!
Wonderful atmosphere and great food. The staff was friendly and helpful.
Great place for lunch enjoyed their outdoor patio.

I think this restaurant is over-rated. I went there for a Sunday brunch. The outdoor area has shade but still humid and hot. The worst part I got six mosquito bites that made my two ankles swollen. The bite scars still remained after three weeks. The main course fried fish was tasty. Though the dessert “bitter sweet” chocolate torte did taste any sweet, only bittter to an unenjoyable level. The waitress was weird. I asked her what coffee they had, which they didn’t have any special brewed coffee. But as I asked, she thought I didn’t know how to order coffee and made me very embarrassed (she literally asked me where I came from). There stars only for the main course. All else worth 0.

My wife surprised me for my birthday with brunch at this place!! It was both our 1st time here but she found this place on social media and come to find out it was a top 10 brunch place in DC!.. well i just got to say it lived up to it!!! You can eat outside,  bar area or downstairs inside.  Very spacious,  clean, fancy looking and the throwback music was awesome! Reminiscing on every tune hahaha. The menu shocked me at 1st because it was so limited but talk about trying something new! Not your usual eggs n bacon spot lol. This place made you step out your comfort zone and it was well worth it! Everything was cooked to perfection! So many flavors in all the meals. Had my tastebuds going crazy!!! Compliments to KEVIN our waiter! For all the help and recommendations! Also Compliments to all the CHEFS!!! Keep up the good work.  My dream is to be a chef and this really inspired me more! They also gave me a bday dessert surprise. This place is just 5 stars! All day!! One of the best brunch spots in DC! For sure!! Thanks Iron Gate!
The food was great. Careful, because the portions are very small. Dont go if you a large appetite.
amazing🌻🌊❤
Sharable foods. Recommend the bread and deviled duck eggs.
Great atmosphere. Hidden outdoor garden in the back. Fabulous food.

Went to Iron Gate last night for restaurant week. The food was delicious. However, we were quite surprised that they were not adequately staffed for restaurant week and their planning for reservations were way off.  When we arrived for our 7 PM reservation we were told we would be seated at 7:30, as they were already running late. They said we could get a drink from the bar and wait outside. There was only one bartender and she was clearly overwhelmed. It took us almost 20 minutes to get two drinks. We were finally seated at 7:45 PM.

First, the history of this house is amazing. From the front door to the patio and the inside of the house the atmosphere is amazing. Iron gate is the ideal place to pick if you are celebrating an anniversary. We chose outdoor sitting, which was perfect on a summer night. Together the hubby and I tried 5 of their cocktails and they were all Amazing! Who ever is the bartender at Iron gate is the best bartender ever. The food sas perfection. Have you ever been to coastal Italy well this are the exact flavours recreated, brought so many flash backs. If you are looking for those authentic Italian coastal flavours this is the place. We ordered the chefs menu, which by the way changes daily. That speaks volumes of what a fantastic chef they have. We are already planning our next visit!
Beautiful courtyard covered in grape vines older than the people working there.  Good Greek and Italian influenced food.  Reasonable prices for lunch.  Just so pleasant.

We came here for our wedding anniversary and from the door to the bar to our table, we had a wonderful experience. Delicious food, fair price to portion ratio for small plate dining, great service and atmosphere, and a splendid surprise at the end since the server knew it was a special dinner. Definitely heading back soon and will be bringing friends.
Attentive team. Portions are small. Drinks are great.
one of the coolest dining spaces in the city

My girlfriends and I were here to celebrate my birthday this past Saturday night. From the first plate to the assorted desserts brought out w a Happy Birthday sign every dish was fabulous. We did the chef's choice family table and it was a flow of excellence. I definitely recommend coming to check out this gem. From entry to exit we had a phenomenal experience.

Iron Gate is one of the best places to eat in DC. With its rotating menu and beautifully constructed plates, you will want to return time and time again. Iron Gate also has fantastic ambiance within its indoor and outdoor seating areas. The service at Iron Gate is also fun, approachable, and exceptionally professional. Overall, experiencing Iron Gate is a must for those looking for a great romantic dinner or those on a food adventure.

I probably lean more toward a 4.5 as opposed to just a 4, but this restaurant isn't quite a 5 either. The ambiance was certainly romantic, service was wonderful, and I loved the cocktail. The ragu for the gnocchi was amazing, but the gnocchi itself was slightly burned. The bison skirt was also tasty. Great location for couples or shall groups. Our group of 6 had to sit on an awkward outdoor sofa, which was fine for hanging out, but made it tough to eat.

We ate in the patio garden, which is a lovely setting. We ordered five of the Carriage Way and Patio tapas. The yogurt dip and bread salad were excellent. The lamb keftedes were very tasty. The squid ink bucattini with smoked salmon was quite good. The blue crab bruschetta was good but nothing special. The quantity of food was quite good and the wine recommendation worked well. This is a really cool spot in Dupont both in terms of the aesthetics and the food quality. It's a small place, so I'd definitely recommend making a reservation. We were a little early for our reservation, so we started at the bar. The cocktails were good, but not convinced they were priced appropriately for their relative simplicity. We were seated right around the time of our reservation. After being seated, I was told by our server that they no longer do a tasting menu, which was a bummer since that was the whole reason we came in the first place (and the website still said that they offer a tasting menu). Instead, we picked 7 dishes (tartare, bruschetta, carrots, haloumi, gnocchi, agnolotti, octopus) split between the two of us + 2 desserts (cherry variation & cheesecake). The gnocchi was a surprisingly large portion for tapas, which was a nice surprise. The octopus was overcooked and tough to chew. Both desserts were good, with the cheesecake being our favorite. I would suggest asking your server about the cherry variation because the menu description is horrible.

I decided to have lunch there because it was listed as one of the best places to eat outdoors and wound up having to sit inside, but I didn't mind a bit. The food and service were excellent! Thandi was such the perfect server and so knowledgeable about the wine selection.
Excellent food and service. Great place.

The ambiance is some of the best in DC! It is a horse stable converted in to a restaurant. The bar, dining hall, and courtyard are all beautiful. It is warm and cozy and adorable. The vibes are perfect for a date or catching up with a close friend. I have also come here with my parents and it's quiet enough that they enjoy it too (without feeling lame). Their house wine (Rizes) is amazing for red or white! It's $9 a glass and fantastic for a house wine.  It's their own private label actually and you can't find it at any of the owner's other restaurants. They don't have happy hour here- but their wine list is worth spending on. The waiters always have good pairing recommendations too.The food is amazing. Not going to lie, it's pricey - maybe even overpriced for the portion size. But the food is sooo tasty. You will need order quite a few plates to be full - I would say 6-8 dishes for 2 people. But the flavors are some of the best in DC. There are also options for vegetarians on the menu too! Iron gate is currently one of my favorite DC restaurants - although pricey it's a place I choose is worth the cost. Love the vibes here and will be back!

Charming little spot! Came here for a small wedding and the staff was lovely. The food was yummy and most of it seemed pretty healthy! But that could have just been what our friends picked to put on the menu. Overall, loved this spot and would like to go back again for date night.

Was not chilled enough.  Waiter took time to chill for us.  Perfect.  When you drink nectar like this, one wine bottle lasts all evening.  Also great wine glasses. Normally not a reviewer but had to come on here to share our experience. I had a trip planned to DC and made reservations for 3 of us at Iron Gate over a month in advance. We saved it for our last night in town because I love Italian food and the restaurant looked like the best way to end our trip!  We arrived five minutes prior to our reservation time at 8:10 and the hostesses told us they could seat us closer to our reservation time. There isn’t much room to stand and wait and the bar was full so it was a bit awkward and felt like we were in the way. Our reservation time came and went and we kept standing awkwardly and waiting. 20 minutes past our reservation the hostesses told us guests were taking a little longer on desert than expected and it would be just a bit longer. At 25 minutes past our reservation time a man seated at the bar approached the hostess stand to say he and his wife had been waiting to be seated 35 minutes past their reservation and asked what was going on, at which point we really grew impatient. We had an event to attend after dinner and at 30 minutes past our reservation we called and got a table at a nearby Italian restaurant, Floriana. We told the hostesses it wasn’t going to work out tonight and left.  When we were seated at Floriana, my phone rang. The manager of Iron Gate called to apologize for the situation, which we thought was very nice. He ended the call by asking where we ended up dining.  Around 15 minutes after the call, the manager of Floriana approached our table and asked if we had come from Iron Gate. We said yes and he presented us with a bottle of wine - the manager from Iron Gate had walked the couple of blocks over to Floriana, told them what happened and asked to purchase wine to compliment our dinner at Floriana. We were astounded! This was truly above and beyond service from Iron Gate. We understand things happen but had been pretty frustrated when we left the restaurant. Thanks to the humility and kindness of the Iron Gate manager, though we never actually dined in, we have nothing but good feelings about Iron Gate and will definitely make it a point to return next time we’re in DC. Thank you to both Iron Gate and Floriana for making it a great last night in town!

Very nice Mediterranean restaurant in DC. It's a high-end restaurant and expensive but the area and ambiance is really nice. Great for dates and group of friends. The food isn't authentic Mediterranean, mainly seafood, but still delicious! Service was great. Rich wine selection too.
Good Greek food and very fun atmosphere. Old wood ceilings.

Finally got to try Iron Gate and went for brunch. Everything was wonderful - tried several dishes both sweet and savory. Riccota hazelnut pancakes were an unexpected favorite. Lots of special touches. Interesting cozy atmosphere and excellent service. The courtyard would be perfect when the weather is nice. The courtyard area is dog friendly and we saw two folks with dogs outside.

Great food and atmosphere. Enjoyed the dates, chilli dip, lamb meatballs, sweet pea bruschetta, and gnocchi. All excellent quality food, very fresh. Everything was awesome, but I was disappointed by the seats at the patio because hanging my jacket on the seat was very awkward.
The sauce is the boss.
Wonderful restuarant. Good drinks. Very friendly staff. Wonderful, creative food. Outdoor patio seating is special.
Small but tasty delicacies. Good service and nice atmosphere. Pasta are the best.
Shared 7 dishes and a snapper among 4 people.  Everything was very good.  A lot of the wine was from Greece and Italy, so we went with a suggestion from our waiter and we really enjoyed it.
Great food, second time here. Helpful attentive staff.
Great food, beautifully presented. Not cheap.

Great place to visit and we met the chef. Food is quite good and wonderful place to visit. Food is great.  Would give 5 stars but couple of dishes had little too much yogurt; BUT again the food is REALLY good; including the personal service.

I went here on a double-date because we lucked out on a prime time reservation and I had heard good things. However, I don’t think it lived up to the hype. We probably spent $600 between a 2 bottles of wine and the suggested portion of …
Great place to grab a bite and an amazing wine list.  Ask for recommendations they will help you in any way they can.  Really really good
Great date spot with an amazing beer, wine, and cocktail list

Terrible experience, we were super excited to celebrate our one anniversary at the iron gate and our experience was not at all what we had imagined. We decided to do the tasting, had no idea that meant it would take 30 minutes between courses and several hours for our dinner. We sat outside to enjoy the rustic evening experience but unfortunately people across from us decided to keep their phone flash lights on the whole time because it was too dark for them outside, (I'm not sure when they didn't just sit inside) the whole time the light was in my face at first I tried to ignore it thinking she would turn it off but the entire 2 hours I was stuck sitting there with a light in my eye. Very aggravating, we asked the manger to move us or ask the people across from us to turn off the flash light he did neither, very disappointing. Later after waiting an hour plus for my entree arrived cold and there was a piece of bone in my food (I'm vegetarian), the manager claimed a piece of their clay oven had chipped and fell in there it wasn't a bone. I'm not sure which is worse. Overall awful experience would not recommend, I felt so bad for my poor fiance he kept apologizing for picking that place.
Excellent meal and service perfect by Oliver et al

Great atmosphere with solid dishes and intriguing cocktails.  Perfectly cooked octopus, unique broccoli anchovy bruschetta. Complimentary birthday cake too!  Edit: Second visit we were seated 45 min after our res but the service was amazing to compensate.  Favourite DC restaurant!
Very romantic restaurant with amazing outdoor seating. The food was an adventure.
Excellent service and good food, some dishes like the oysters and octopus are extraordinarily good.

Always nice to come back.  Brought my old neighbor from Sausalito, CA here for a catch up date.  She loved it and so did I.  Our server was a bit “self possessed” but did his job dragging a bit.  In any case still a great lave.
Went here for Valentine's dinner. Awesome time. Very interesting signature drinks. The fixed menu was excellent. Met my pescatarin dietary requirements. Both of us enjoyed it. Service was very good.
Awesome ambiance in the carriage house, outside patio under the vines, or at the bar.  Great place for drinks, dinner with friends, or an intimate meal.  Highly recommend!

Our first experience here was really great - we did a 7 or so course tasting menu with wine pairings.  Waaaay to much dessert.  Some of the wines were good.  Really nice portion sizes.  Second time we had a large party on the garden patio and the food was good but service was missing.  We still had a nice time.  We considered having a large reception here but the communication has been poor so we're moving on to somewhere else.  I'd probably still go here for a romantic dinner with my other half - but not to throw a party.
Went there for brunch and it was incredible. Everything we ordered was delicious and the atmosphere is so cozy in the way back room. Definitely recommend this place.

Excellent food! Definitely more $$$ than $$ because the plates are fairly small but that ends up being a huge plus when you taste all of them. Best tartare and crudo, which can be hard to find. Very professional staff; options for tasting menu.
Perfect ambiance for date night. The arancini is outstanding.

Excellent wine selection and extremely knowledgeable wait staff who give such colorful descriptions of both food and drinks.  The portions of appetizers can be a bit skimpy,  but everything tastes great.
Great spot, definitely try to get a spot outside.
The oysters are amazing!

First timer and enjoyed it. Its restataunt week tried the fried oysters.  Very very good. Love the interior.  Bar was well stocked. Clearly great place for date night you will earn cool points if its a first date and you typically dont frewunt the DC scene. Price point coukd get up to $$$$. Parking will be a challenge. Lyft or uber to avoid rounding the block. Service was very good and some hidden surprises once inside past the bar.
Very neat place. The overall ambience is nice for all ages.
Nice little cocktail spot with a cute little outdoor patio area with small fire pits for chilly nights. Haven't done much food there, good first date spot though

I came to Iron Gate after I gave up trying to find a bar in DuPont that wasn't insanely packed or one in which I didn't have to yell to talk to the person I'm with.  Iron Gate fit the bill perfectly; you've got a long, narrow spot with a decently sized, quaint bar and a few tables on either end.  The food is excellent-- it is pricey and portions are small but that's standard fare at this sort of establishment. The old fashioned that I had was very good and the wine selection is expansive. If you're looking for a place to take someone that's a bit more upscale and relaxed than your standard DC fare, Iron Gate is a solid bet (just be prepared to pay extra).
Poor service great food.
Delicious dinner, we had the family style. Nice atmosphere, wonderful service
Fantastic food and service in a charming setting. My wife and I really enjoyed the number of vegetarian dish options, from burrata, to gnocchi, to the harissa carrot dish.
Beautiful ambiance. The place had so much character, with great food the experience was memorable. Also got a beautiful birthday dessert complimentary!!

Definitely a unique dining experience. Unexpected food combinations. Sophisticated yet simple play of ingredients. If you want typical fish or prime rib this us definitely NOT the place for you.  However, if you like the surprise of the unexpected like octopus salad and parsley salad or roasted dates filled with feta, then surely give this place a try.
Go there! Say Arron V sent you (if Melissa is there, you might get a drink :)
Sunday December 17, 2017, 11:37am: Wanted to book reservations for my girlfriends birthday. A guy picked up and placed me on hold and never came back.
Amazing food great ambiance ... but DC prices lol save this spot for special occasions lol !

Wonderful experience from start to finish! We had the almost all the vegetarian dishes on the menu and their were several...and we were more than pleased. The favorites were the brussel sprout salad, burrata dish, the gnocchi and the squash lasagna! Service was excellent!
Absolutely fantastic food. Service is superb. Parking can be an issue.
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente

Unique atmosphere in the bar area; cocktails are fantastic, but can get crowded. The back is a garden, and reasonably nice, but it's almost too big, and the crowd is super pretentious and rather dressy, if that's your thing. The food is extraordinary; well thought out and creative. Worth a visit.
Excellent accommodation of our vegan requests
The service is terrific, excellent food. Worth the money
Knowledgeable staff with a great menu.
Greasr hidden gem. Good food and wonderful setting.

Dined here for my parent's anniversary. We got several small plates and the mixed grill, all of which were excellent. While we had more than enough food, some of the small plates were a little pricey for their portion size, namely the eggplant dish and the deviled eggs. There is also a short in the wiring in the main dining room that causes the low hanging pendant lights to flicker. They were more than accommodating with moving us to a table without an overhead pendant. I would hope that's something that can be fixed in the near future as diners who arrived after us did not have the option to move. Aside from that everything was good. They ended our dinner with a complimentary anniversary dessert which was a nice way to end the meal.
